+## Design Standards (UI/UX Pro Level)
+- Quality target: Linear.app, Raycast.com, Arc.net level
+- Dark mode primary with the brand colors from above
+- Use shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion + lucide-react
+- NEVER use interactive CLIs or prompts. If a command may prompt, use non-interactive flags or edit files manually instead.
+- The Next.js scaffold has already been prepared when needed. Improve the existing project in-place instead of trying to create it again.
+- Hero: stunning gradient background matching brand, animated entrance with staggered reveals
+- Features: bento grid or card grid with icons, hover effects, micro-interactions
+- Pricing: show ALL tiers together (monthly/yearly/lifetime) with toggle or tabs
+- Use the app's actual promotional images — they are professionally designed
+- Mobile-first responsive
+- SEO meta tags, Open Graph, Twitter cards
+- Smooth scroll animations (fade-in, slide-up on viewport enter)
+- Glassmorphism cards with subtle backdrop-blur
+- Consistent spacing scale (use Tailwind spacing: 4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 24)
+- Typography hierarchy: display → heading → body → caption
+- Subtle grain/noise texture on hero background for depth
+- Hover states on ALL interactive elements (scale, glow, color shift)
+- Keyboard accessible (focus-visible rings on tab navigation)
+
+## Current request:
+Rebuild the landing page completely from scratch. Make it WORLD-CLASS.
+
+STORE LINKS:
+- iOS: Coming Soon
+- Android: Coming Soon
+App is NOT LAUNCHED YET.
+
+Build all sections: Navbar, Hero (with app screenshots), Features (bento grid), Screenshots Gallery, Pricing (all tiers together), Downloads, FAQ, Footer.
+Setup shadcn/ui + framer-motion + lucide-react first. Run npm run build at the end.
+
+Make the requested changes. After making changes, briefly summarize what you changed (1-3 bullet points).

